The paper discusses the use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) to automatically determine solver schedules for Boolean Constraint Technology. ASP is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also involves optimization problems (cs.LO) and data mining (cs.DM) in determining the schedules. Additionally, the paper involves programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) in the implementation of the approach.
